<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-55-0838 </DOCNO><TEXT>The heating costs for trade and industrial sheds or hangars have become,during the past years, due to rising energy prices, an increasingly perceptiblecost factor, which is reflected in increased production costs and oftenin an impairment of the efficiency or even the competitiveness of a businessenterprise. The report presents an up-to-date possibility of reducingthese heating costs by up to 40%, as has been proved. The particularadvantage of this technique consists in the fact that also the wall andceiling air heater already installed can be reconstructed without greatconversion effort and therefore inexpensively.</TEXT></DOC>